definition: Index giving the final direction of gaze as the dot probe is presented.
Trial level gaze bias score, using the weighted method. from the itrak package.
Operating system used. Data parsed from os_version.
The operating system and version used. Uses User-Agent request header.
Returns the GPU onboard the computer. Uses WebGL API.
Category identifying the GPU as either separate from the CPU or intergrated. Uses WebGL API. Data parsed from

The browser and version. Derived from User-Agent request header.
The ratio between physical pixels and device independent pixels in the current display. Uses Window.devicePixelRatio from Web API.
Returns the width and height of the screen. Uses Window.screen.height [and width] from Web API.
Returns the width and height of the browser window. Uses Window.innerHeight [and innerHeight] from Web API.
The total bytes used by JavaScript on the task. Uses window.performance.memory from Google.
Maximum size a JavaScript heap accessable by the task. Uses window.performance.memory from Google.
String indicating the success or failure of accessing the webcam and the reason for it (i.e. getUserMediaFailed).
Returns the width and height of the webcam. Uses the HTMLVideoElement API.
Returns the brand of webcam being used. Uses the MediaStream API.
The perceived brightness distribution or "luminosity" within an image, normalized from 0 (black) to 1 (white).
Returns whether or not the task has been minimized or a new tab has been open and is visible. Uses the Page Visibility API.
Whether or not the task was calibrated.
Whether or not the webcam was initiated.
